The paper deals with the analysis of a leader election algorithm, which involves data structures and graph theory (cs.DS and cs.GT). The authors also use information theory (cs.IT) to derive upper bounds on the number of survivors in the algorithm. The Rice method, which is used in the paper, is a statistical method that is often used in computer science for analyzing algorithms and data structures (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses a property of a general urns and balls problem, which is a classic problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
